clinical_study.brief_title: Safety and Tolerability of ODM-201 in Castrate Resistant Prostate Cancer; Extension Study to Study 3104001
clinical_study.official_title: Safety and Tolerability of ODM-201 in Patients With Castrate Resistant Prostate Cancer: Open, Non-randomised, Uncontrolled, Multicentre, Extension Study to Study 3104001

brief_summary.textblock: The purpose of this study is to evaluate safety and tolerability of ODM-201 in patients with castrate resistant prostate cancer.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Participants With Adverse Events
primary_outcome.time_frame: From first dose of study treatment up to 4 weeks after last dose of study treatment
primary_outcome.description: Adverse events from start of ODM-201 treatment (in ARADES 3104001 study) until end of study visit (in ARADES-EXT 3104002 study). Median duration on study treatment was 11,0 months.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Written informed consent
- Successful completion of study protocol 3104001
- Response or stable disease in study 3104001 at week 12
Exclusion Criteria:
- New serious concurrent medical condition
- Not able to swallow the study drug

overall_official.affiliation: Gustave Roussy, Cancer Campus, Grand Paris

participant_flow.recruitment_details: Participants were enrolled at 17 hospitals in Europe and in the USA
participant_flow.pre_assignment_details: Patients with response or stable disease at week 12 in ARADES 3104001 study as judged by the investigator, were allowed to continue in the ARADES-EXT 3104002 extension study.
